      </prefercite>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_6158b8719fa53ed7214543bdd8bbd835">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <bioghist id="aspace_cc80f5fd44d308aaaea8b10c03fa3010">
         <head>WALLACE THURMAN (1902-1934)</head>
         <p>Wallace Thurman was a novelist and playwright who found fame before his early death with the novel <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>The Blacker the Berry</part>
            </title> and the play, "Harlem". A biographical sketch of Thurman written by Harold Jackman, can be found in folder 59 of this collection.</p>  
      </bioghist>
